2. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a system for aiding static analysis tools, which is related to software engineering. 
3. cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses code hiding techniques like packing, dynamic loading, self modifying, and reflection, which are related to programming languages. 
4. cs.SD (Software Development): The paper proposes a system for aiding static analysis tools, which is related to software development. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses a system that leverages just-in-time collection to extract data and bytecode from an application at runtime, which is related to systems and control.
